perfect story post katrina my children have had to deal with tremendous unexpected changes in our lives as our home was destroyed by hurricane katrina . one day we were in a home and my four year olds were just getting settled into school . the next day we were living 500 miles away from home , their home was destroyed , and they were placed in new schools . this story was perfect in explaining to them that change happens to everyone . sometimes these changes are very unexpected . if we are willing to embrace change we can make this change an opportunity rather than a tragedy . wonderful principles to teach to kids . my wife and i learned from it also